WEBVTT

00:02.469 --> 00:05.105
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"NECESSARY ROUGHNESS"...</i>

00:06.239 --> 00:07.240
NICO, I NEED SOMEBODY LIKE YOU
TO COME WORK FOR ME.

00:08.108 --> 00:08.441
Nico: MARK CUBAN
OFFERED ME A JOB...

00:09.209 --> 00:10.243
IN DALLAS.
ARE YOU GONNA TAKE IT?

00:11.011 --> 00:11.344
NOT SURE
WHAT'S LEFT FOR ME HERE.

00:12.479 --> 00:14.547
I THINK YOU'RE LOOKING
FOR AN EXCUSE FOR THIS TO FAIL

00:14.581 --> 00:17.117
BECAUSE YOU'RE STILL IN LOVE
WITH SOMEONE ELSE.

00:17.150 --> 00:19.185
DINNER TONIGHT?
JUST THE TWO OF US?
YES.

00:22.589 --> 00:24.357
Nico: IT'S NICO CARELES,
MR. CUBAN.

00:24.391 --> 00:25.358
I'M IN.

00:26.359 --> 00:27.594
Man: YOU'LL NEED TO COME
WITH US.

00:35.235 --> 00:38.471
DIVISION CHAMPS.
CONFERENCE CHAMPS.

00:38.505 --> 00:43.176
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT SAYS TO ME?
WE<i>ALMOST</i>WON.

00:43.209 --> 00:48.381
GENTLEMEN...
NOBODY REMEMBERS SECOND PLACE.

00:48.415 --> 00:52.652
FROM NOW ON,
WE CELEBRATE A CHAMPIONSHIP,

00:52.686 --> 00:54.254
OR WE DON'T CELEBRATE.

00:54.287 --> 00:55.255
IS THAT CLEAR?

00:55.288 --> 00:57.691
All: YES, COACH!
IS THAT CLEAR?!

00:57.724 --> 00:59.225
All: YES, COACH!

00:59.259 --> 01:01.428
THIS GUY'S ABOUT AS MUCH FUN
AS A HEMORRHOID.

01:01.461 --> 01:04.631
YEAH, HE'S GONNA BE
LIVING UP OUR ASSES.

01:04.664 --> 01:06.433
NEW OWNERSHIP
FELT LIKE COACH PURNELL

01:06.466 --> 01:08.234
HAD TAKEN THIS TEAM
AS FAR AS HE COULD.

01:08.268 --> 01:10.670
TOM WIZINSKI
HAS 10 PLAYOFF RUNS,

01:10.704 --> 01:13.239
4 CHAMPIONSHIP RINGS.

01:13.273 --> 01:16.910
OKAY, SO, WHAT?
HE JUST PACKED UP AND LEFT?

01:16.943 --> 01:19.446
WELL, THEY GAVE HIM A NICE
BUYOUT. HE'LL LAND SOMEWHERE.

01:19.479 --> 01:21.548
YOU DON'T SEEM
PARTICULARLY UPSET.

01:21.581 --> 01:23.550
TRADES, HIRINGS,
AND FIRINGS --

01:23.583 --> 01:28.121
THE ONLY CONSTANT IN FOOTBALL,
DANI, IS CHANGE.

01:32.392 --> 01:33.560
YOU WERE ALL ASKED
TO BRING AN ITEM

01:33.593 --> 01:35.128
THAT REPRESENTED LAST SEASON.

01:36.196 --> 01:37.464
HAS EVERYONE BROUGHT SOMETHING
AND PUT IT IN THE BIN?

01:37.497 --> 01:39.432
All: YES, COACH!

01:39.466 --> 01:42.635
GOOD.
HENRY, DO THE HONORS.

01:42.669 --> 01:46.773
[ LIGHTER CLICKS ]
LAST YEAR...IS HISTORY.

01:46.806 --> 01:48.508
[ METAL CLANGS ]

01:49.542 --> 01:51.378
THOSE GLOVES HELPED ME
CATCH 300 PASSES

01:51.411 --> 01:52.645
IN THE LAST 3 SEASONS!

01:52.679 --> 01:54.547
AND YET THEY NEVER
SNAGGED YOU A RING,

01:54.581 --> 01:55.648
NOW, DID THEY, MR. KING?

01:55.682 --> 02:01.488
LAST YEAR IS A BAD DREAM
THAT JUST WENT UP IN SMOKE.

02:01.521 --> 02:03.390
THIS IS A NEW TEAM.

02:03.423 --> 02:08.428
THE FUTURE
IS ALL ABOUT WINNING.

02:08.461 --> 02:10.196
ALL RIGHT, STRETCH THEM OUT.
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

02:10.230 --> 02:12.565
Man: COME ON, BOYS!
HUSTLE UP! GET OUT THERE!

02:12.599 --> 02:16.770
COACH WIZINSKI, I'D LIKE FOR YOU
TO MEET DR. DANI SANTINO.

02:16.803 --> 02:18.738
HEY.
UH, LET ME HAVE
THOSE REPORTS, JIMMY.

02:18.772 --> 02:21.207
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

02:21.241 --> 02:22.342
SO, TEAM THERAPIST,
HUH?

02:23.476 --> 02:24.411
THEY, UH -- THEY COME TO YOU
WHEN THEY HAVE MOMMY ISSUES?

02:25.378 --> 02:27.580
ACTUALLY, THEY COME TO ME
WITH ANY ISSUES.

02:27.614 --> 02:28.782
YOU KNOW,
FOOTBALL AT THIS LEVEL

02:29.883 --> 02:31.484
REQUIRES BOTH PHYSICAL
<i>AND</i>MENTAL FITNESS,

02:31.518 --> 02:32.686
AS I'M SURE YOU KNOW.

02:32.719 --> 02:34.821
WELL, YOU KNOW,
I-I SHAKE A LOT OF HANDS.

02:34.854 --> 02:38.391
PEOPLE ARE ALWAYS AMAZED
AT HOW STRONG MY FINGERS ARE.

02:38.425 --> 02:40.293
YOU KNOW HOW
THEY GOT THAT WAY?

02:40.326 --> 02:43.296
YEARS OF CARRYING AROUND
THIS KIND OF HARDWARE.

02:43.329 --> 02:44.831
GOT THREE MORE OF THEM
IN MY TROPHY CASE.

02:44.864 --> 02:47.567
PLANNING ON GETTING
ONE MORE FOR MY THUMB.

02:47.600 --> 02:50.537
I'M HERE TO MAKE WINNERS
OUT OF THIS TEAM.

02:50.570 --> 02:54.574
AND TO WIN,
PLAYERS NEED IT SIMPLE.

02:54.607 --> 02:57.377
THERE ARE NO SECRETS
FROM ME.

02:57.410 --> 03:01.581
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT, COACH,
THE THERAPIST/CLIENT PRIVILEGE

03:01.614 --> 03:05.385
IS NOT AN OPTION
LIKE COLE SLAW OR POTATO SALAD.

03:05.418 --> 03:07.287
IT IS
AN IRONCLAD RULE.

03:07.320 --> 03:08.722
SO IF YOU ARE SUGGESTING

03:08.755 --> 03:12.292
THAT I BECOME
SOME SORT OF STOOL PIGEON,

03:12.325 --> 03:12.359
THAT AIN'T GONN' FLY.

03:14.294 --> 03:16.296
OH, OKAY.

03:17.330 --> 03:18.732
THEN YOU'RE FIRED.

03:18.765 --> 03:20.033
[ SLOAN'S "BELIEVE IN ME"
PLAYS ]

03:20.066 --> 03:21.267
EXCUSE ME?

03:21.301 --> 03:24.504
I JUST DID.

03:25.538 --> 03:26.706
COACH.

03:27.774 --> 03:29.509
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

03:32.045 --> 03:37.050
* IF YOU BELIEVE
EVERYTHING HAS A REASON *

03:37.083 --> 03:40.387
* IF YOU BELIEVE THAT
WHAT YOU SEE WILL UNFOLD *

03:40.420 --> 03:41.654
[ DOORBELL RINGING ]

03:42.856 --> 03:44.791
* IF YOU BELIEVE THAT EVERYBODY
NEEDS TO SHAKE IT LOOSE *

03:44.824 --> 03:47.627
OH, THANK GOD! OH!

03:47.660 --> 03:48.828
GOOD THING
OUR VACATION PLANS

03:48.862 --> 03:51.765
COINCIDED
WITH YOUR NERVOUS BREAKDOWN.

03:51.798 --> 03:54.734
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

03:57.404 --> 03:59.539
[ BEEP ]

03:59.572 --> 04:01.341
HEY.

04:02.742 --> 04:06.780
WELL, IT'S BEEN A WHILE,
BUT I CAN MAKE AN INTRODUCTION.

04:06.813 --> 04:09.883
I'LL MAKE THAT HAPPEN.

04:09.916 --> 04:11.885
[ BEEP ]

04:16.556 --> 04:17.824
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

04:17.857 --> 04:20.627
SHOULD WE REALLY BE DRINKING
AT 11:00 AM?

04:20.660 --> 04:21.895
MATT KNOCKS UP NOELLE

04:23.063 --> 04:23.763
JUST AS YOU'RE ABOUT
TO GET BACK TOGETHER...
MM-HMM.

04:24.564 --> 04:26.633
...MARRIES HER, TO BOOT.
OH, RIGHT.

04:26.666 --> 04:28.568
YOUR SON RUNS OFF
WITH AN HEIRESS,

04:28.601 --> 04:30.470
AND YOU GET FIRED
FROM THE HAWKS.

04:30.503 --> 04:32.639
I WAS THERE.
I DON'T NEED THE RECAP.

04:32.672 --> 04:34.774
ALL I'M SAYING
IS YOU HAVE A-PLUS REASONS

04:34.808 --> 04:37.344
FOR HEAVY DRINKING,
REGARDLESS OF THE HOUR.

04:38.378 --> 04:40.714
SALUD.
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:40.747 --> 04:42.682
MM.

04:42.716 --> 04:45.685
BUT WE DON'T HAVE TO HAVE
A PITY PARTY OR ANYTHING

04:45.719 --> 04:47.454
BECAUSE I'M GONNA
PUT SOME FEELERS OUT

04:47.487 --> 04:48.555
TO SOME OTHER TEAMS,

04:48.588 --> 04:50.790
AND, YOU KNOW,
I'M GONNA BE FINE.

04:50.824 --> 04:52.625
PFFT -- THE HAWKS WILL BE
CALLING YOU IN NO TIME,

04:52.659 --> 04:53.960
BEGGING YOU
TO COME BACK.

04:53.993 --> 04:56.563
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THAT.
IT'S BEEN A WEEK.

04:56.596 --> 04:58.498
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]
SEE? I BET THAT'S THEM NOW.

04:59.899 --> 05:01.835
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
THIS IS DANI.

05:01.868 --> 05:05.438
NICO: You still in the
helping-people business, Doctor?

05:05.472 --> 05:06.606
NICO?

05:06.639 --> 05:08.508
I know.
It's been a long time.

05:08.541 --> 05:10.710
WHERE ARE YOU?
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

05:10.744 --> 05:13.513
There's a limo in your driveway.
I need you to get in.

05:13.546 --> 05:16.416
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
THERE'S A LIMO IN MY DRIVEWAY?

05:16.449 --> 05:18.485
[ HORN HONKS ]
[ GASPS ] THERE'S A LIMO
IN YOUR DRIVEWAY!

05:18.518 --> 05:20.820
I'M SORRY.
WHY AM I GONNA GET IN A LIMO?

05:20.854 --> 05:22.922
Because
I need your help.

05:22.956 --> 05:24.391
* LET'S GO!

05:25.158 --> 05:26.559
* EVERYBODY, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON *

05:27.494 --> 05:29.896
* EVERYBODY IN THE HOUSE,
START IT UP NOW *

05:29.929 --> 05:33.466
* EVERYBODY, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON *

05:33.500 --> 05:36.736
* EVERYBODY IN THE HOUSE,
START IT UP NOW *

05:36.770 --> 05:39.773
* EVERYBODY, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON *

05:39.806 --> 05:42.575
* EVERYBODY IN THE HOUSE,
START IT UP NOW *

05:42.609 --> 05:44.477
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
* EVERYBODY, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON *

05:44.511 --> 05:45.679
HELLO.

05:45.712 --> 05:47.814
HI. WELCOME TO V3.
CAN I HELP YOU?

05:47.847 --> 05:51.184
UH, ACCORDING TO MY DRIVER,
I'M SUPPOSED TO SEE, UM...

05:51.217 --> 05:53.553
Connor: DR. SANTINO.
YEAH?

05:53.586 --> 05:54.788
OVER HERE.
HELLO?

05:54.821 --> 05:57.791
HELLO. AH.
THE SAVIOR HAS ARRIVED.

05:57.824 --> 05:58.958
WAIT RIGHT THERE.

05:58.992 --> 06:00.593
OKAY.

06:03.530 --> 06:05.999
I'M GLAD YOU COULD ACCEPT
MY INVITATION.

06:06.032 --> 06:09.202
I'M CONNOR McCLANE.
WELCOME TO V3.

06:09.235 --> 06:13.540
* BABY, WORK YOUR MAGIC ON ME

06:17.944 --> 06:21.948
SO,
V3 IS SPORTS MANAGEMENT?

06:21.981 --> 06:23.750
WELL, THAT'S LIKE SAYING
APPLE MAKES COMPUTERS.

06:23.783 --> 06:25.752
I MEAN, SURE, WE HANDLE THE BEST
ATHLETES ON THE PLANET --

06:25.785 --> 06:29.522
THE FOUR BIGS, PLUS SOCCER,
TENNIS, GOLF, EVEN CRICKET.

06:29.556 --> 06:31.858
SOMEONE'S GOT TO TEACH ME
THE RULES OF CRICKET.
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:31.891 --> 06:34.661
ALSO, WE'RE A GLOBAL LEADER
IN FASHION,

06:34.694 --> 06:35.862
MEDIA, ENTERTAINMENT.

06:35.895 --> 06:37.230
WE GOT OUR FINGERS IN --

06:37.263 --> 06:38.765
IT LOOKS LIKE
YOU HAVE A QUESTION.

06:38.798 --> 06:40.533
ONLY ONE.

06:40.567 --> 06:42.535
CONNOR, I NEED FIVE MINUTES
ON THE LeBRON THING.

06:42.569 --> 06:43.737
GONNA HAVE TO HAPPEN
AFTER LUNCH.

06:43.770 --> 06:44.838
ALL RIGHT, GO AHEAD.
YOU WERE SAYING?

06:45.905 --> 06:47.807
UH, I WAS ASKING, UH,
WHAT EXACTLY AM I DOING HERE?

06:47.841 --> 06:49.676
GOOD QUE--
HOLD ON ONE SEC.

06:49.709 --> 06:52.712
[ BEEP ]
BOBBY, LOOK. WE BOTH KNOW
THE DEAL IS A NONSTARTER.

06:52.746 --> 06:53.880
AND, QUITE FRANKLY,
I'M INSULTED.

06:53.913 --> 06:55.949
NOW, YOU BRING BACK SOMETHING
THAT INSULTS BOTH OF US,

06:55.982 --> 06:57.617
AND MAYBE WE HAVE A DEAL,
OKAY?

06:57.650 --> 06:58.685
GOODBYE.
[ BEEP ]

06:59.619 --> 07:00.687
SORRY. YOU HAVE
MY UNDIVIDED ATTENTION.

07:01.521 --> 07:02.589
WAS THAT GUY ON MUTE
THE WHOLE TIME?

07:03.623 --> 07:05.759
CAN I OFFER YOU SOMETHING
TO DRINK? WATER, SODA?

07:05.792 --> 07:07.594
SPIRULINA HEMP SHAKE?
UH, NOPE. I'M GOOD.

07:07.627 --> 07:09.963
JASMINE, HOLD ALL MY CALLS,
AND SEE IF YOU CAN FIND SOMEONE

07:09.996 --> 07:13.533
TO TEACH ME THE RULES OF CRICKET
OVER DINNER, WILL YOU?
RIGHT AWAY.

07:13.566 --> 07:14.768
AH, PERFECT TIMING.

07:14.801 --> 07:17.570
DR. SANTINO, THIS IS MY C.F.O.,
TROY CUTLER.

07:17.604 --> 07:19.272
HI.
I'M THE BIG-IDEA GUY.

07:19.305 --> 07:20.674
TROY EXECUTES.

07:20.707 --> 07:22.776
AH. WELL,
THAT SOUNDS OMINOUS.

07:22.809 --> 07:24.644
IN OTHER WORDS, HE SCHMOOZES
AND GIVES MAGAZINE INTERVIEWS.

07:24.678 --> 07:26.079
I ACTUALLY WORK FOR A LIVING.

07:26.112 --> 07:30.116
I'M SORRY.
UH, THIS TOUR HAS BEEN LOVELY.

07:30.150 --> 07:33.086
BUT I'M ACTUALLY WONDERING
WHY I'M HERE.

07:35.622 --> 07:38.091
DR. SANTINO, HAVE YOU EVER
SEEN $100 MILLION BEFORE?

07:38.124 --> 07:39.592
MNH.

07:39.626 --> 07:41.027
WELL,
YOU'RE LOOKING AT IT.

07:41.061 --> 07:44.030
EACH OF THESE FOLDERS
IS A MULTIMILLION-DOLLAR OFFER

07:44.064 --> 07:46.599
FROM A PREMIUM BRAND.
OKAY.

07:46.633 --> 07:48.935
WE HAVE AN 18-YEAR-OLD
PITCHING PHENOM --
DARRYL HUTCHINSON.

07:48.968 --> 07:51.037
KILLER ATTITUDE
AND A 100-MILE-AN-HOUR FASTBALL.

07:51.071 --> 07:54.574
HE'S PROBABLY GOING FIRST IN
THE BASEBALL DRAFT NEXT MONTH --

07:54.607 --> 07:55.709
MAKE HIM
AN OVERNIGHT MILLIONAIRE

07:55.742 --> 07:57.644
AND A LIKELY SUPERSTAR.

07:57.677 --> 08:00.647
THE THING IS, THE KID
IS HAIR-ON-FIRE TERRIFIED

08:00.680 --> 08:01.981
ABOUT GETTING
ON AN AIRPLANE.

08:02.015 --> 08:04.884
AH. AWAY GAMES --
THAT'S A BIG PROBLEM.

08:04.918 --> 08:07.754
YEAH. IF THE KID CAN'T FLY,
HE CAN'T PLAY PRO BALL.

08:07.787 --> 08:10.090
ALL 20 FOLDERS GO BYE-BYE.

08:10.123 --> 08:11.157
RUMORS
ARE ALREADY STARTING

08:12.625 --> 08:13.560
TO FLOAT AROUND THE LEAGUE
THAT THE KID'S A HEAD CASE.

08:14.494 --> 08:15.095
NOW, IF WE CAN'T GET HIM
ON A PLANE NEXT WEEK

08:16.329 --> 08:18.598
FOR HIS TRYOUTS IN KANSAS CITY,
HIS DRAFT STATUS WILL PLUMMET,

08:18.631 --> 08:22.135
COST THE KID MILLIONS,
MAYBE EVEN HIS WHOLE CAREER.

08:22.168 --> 08:24.771
THAT IS WHY YOU'RE HERE.

08:26.106 --> 08:28.908
LOOP, SWOOP, PULL!
RIGHT FOOT FORWARD!

08:28.942 --> 08:31.044
LOOP, SWOOP, PULL!

08:31.077 --> 08:32.912
WHAT ARE WE DOING?

08:32.946 --> 08:34.914
WE'RE DIGGING FOR FROGS.

08:34.948 --> 08:36.916
WHAT DOES IT LOOK LIKE WE'RE
DOING? WE'RE TYING OUR SHOES.

08:36.950 --> 08:38.818
YEAH, I KNOW WE'RE
TYING OUR SHOES, BUT WHY?

08:38.852 --> 08:39.953
MR. KING.

08:40.954 --> 08:42.055
YOU'RE LATE.

08:42.088 --> 08:43.823
NYET.
I'M RIGHT ON TIME, COACH.

08:43.857 --> 08:46.159
NO. 10 MINUTES EARLY
IS ON TIME.

08:46.192 --> 08:46.226
SEE PAGE THREE
OF THE WIZINSKI BIBLE,

08:48.828 --> 08:49.963
WHICH WAS E-MAILED
TO EVERYONE LAST NIGHT.

08:51.064 --> 08:51.097
AH, THAT'S A PROBLEM.
YOU SHOULD HAVE TWEETED IT.

08:52.132 --> 08:52.165
I'M NOT REALLY CHECKING
THE E-MAIL THESE DAYS.

08:52.766 --> 08:53.967
KIND OF 2012, YOU KNOW?

08:54.968 --> 08:56.870
YEAH, SEE PAGE 11 --
SHOE TYING.
[ LAUGHS ]

08:56.903 --> 08:58.204
WELL, I DON'T REALLY
HAVE TO TIE THE SHOES

08:58.238 --> 08:59.973
'CAUSE I'VE GOT
THESE DOPE VELCRO STRAPS.

09:00.006 --> 09:02.876
NO, VELCRO IS FOR PEOPLE
UNDER 8 AND OVER 80,

09:02.909 --> 09:04.878
NOT PRO ATHLETES.

09:04.911 --> 09:06.646
ON THE LINE!

09:06.680 --> 09:07.814
[ ALL GROANING ]

09:08.948 --> 09:13.086
SINCE MR. KING SHOWED UP LATE,
WEARING THE WRONG SHOES,

09:13.119 --> 09:16.656
EVERYONE RUNS UNTIL HE GETS BACK
WITH THE RIGHT ONES.

09:16.690 --> 09:17.957
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

09:17.991 --> 09:21.027
DON'T STAND THERE
LIKE A JACKASS. GO!

09:23.129 --> 09:25.632
[ APPLAUSE ]

09:25.665 --> 09:28.101
WHAT'S HAPPENING?
WE JUST SIGNED

09:28.134 --> 09:29.703
THE HEISMAN TROPHY WINNER
FROM ALABAMA.

09:31.037 --> 09:32.972
IT'S A LITTLE TRADITION
WE DO HERE

09:33.006 --> 09:35.208
I LIKE TO CALL
"THE WELCOME HOME."

09:35.241 --> 09:37.077
AND YOU DO THIS
FOR ALL YOUR CLIENTS?

09:37.110 --> 09:38.945
MM-HMM, AND EMPLOYEES, TOO,
WHEN THEY SIGN HERE.

09:38.978 --> 09:39.946
HUH.

09:39.979 --> 09:43.083
SO, DARYL HUTCHINSON.

09:43.116 --> 09:45.085
WELL, I HAVE DECIDED

09:45.118 --> 09:47.187
THAT I WILL TAKE ON
YOUR CLIENT AS MY CLIENT.

09:47.220 --> 09:48.221
BUT I GOT TO ASK YOU,

09:48.254 --> 09:51.157
WHAT DOES NICO CARELES
HAVE TO DO WITH ANY OF THIS?

09:51.191 --> 09:54.728
ASK HIM YOURSELF.

09:56.096 --> 09:58.231
Man: WHOO!

09:58.264 --> 10:00.934
UH, WILL YOU EXCUSE ME
FOR JUST A SEC?
SURE.

10:05.138 --> 10:07.140
THIS DUDE IS A MOFO!

10:07.173 --> 10:09.743
BY "MOFO,"
I ASSUME YOU MEAN WIZINSKI.

10:09.776 --> 10:12.045
YES.
HE'S CRAZY. HE'S LOCO.

10:12.078 --> 10:14.147
HE -- HE'S UNBALANCED.
HE'S DERANGED.

10:14.180 --> 10:16.783
HE'S CRACKED IN THE CABEZA.
YOU GOT TO DO SOMETHING.

10:16.816 --> 10:19.953
HE'S A DERANGED MANIAC.
I'LL GET RIGHT ON THAT.

10:19.986 --> 10:21.154
YOU THINK
THIS IS FUNNY?

10:21.187 --> 10:23.757
"T," HE'S OUR HEAD COACH
AND OUR G.M.

10:23.790 --> 10:26.159
ALL RIGHT, HIS METHODS
MAY BE A LITTLE UNORTHODOX,

10:26.192 --> 10:27.761
BUT HE'S A PROVEN WINNER.

10:27.794 --> 10:30.063
HE HAS TURNED AROUND
THREE LOSING TEAMS.

10:30.096 --> 10:33.967
AND MORE IMPORTANT,
HE'S HERE TO STAY.

10:34.000 --> 10:35.869
I THINK YOU GOT
TO ASK YOURSELF --

10:35.902 --> 10:37.771
ARE YOU GONNA
BE THE KID

10:37.804 --> 10:38.972
WHO KEEPS GETTING
KICKED OUT OF CLASS,

10:39.005 --> 10:40.907
OR DO YOU WANT TO
GET WITH THE PROGRAM?

10:40.940 --> 10:43.209
FINE.

10:43.243 --> 10:45.145
BUT IF I GOT TO DEAL
WITH COACH CRAZY,

10:45.178 --> 10:47.247
I NEED TO SEE DR. D.
THAT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

10:47.280 --> 10:48.815
I NEED TO SEE DR. D.!
NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

10:49.883 --> 10:51.217
LOOK. WIZINSKI IS BRINGING IN
HIS OWN GUY FROM CHICAGO.

10:52.852 --> 10:54.020
HE'S SUPPOSED TO BE ONE OF
THE BEST SPORTS SHRINKS IN THE
BUSINESS -- A DR. McTAVISH.

10:55.188 --> 10:58.792
I AM NOT GONNA DOWNLOAD
TO SOME FOOL I DON'T EVEN KNOW!

10:58.825 --> 11:02.162
THAT'S WHAT YOU SAID
BEFORE YOU TALKED TO DANI.

11:02.195 --> 11:03.930
Dani: EXCUSE ME.

11:03.963 --> 11:05.098
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

11:08.001 --> 11:09.969
EXCUSE ME.
EXCUSE ME. YEAH.

11:11.338 --> 11:13.239
Nico: HELLO, DOCTOR.

11:13.273 --> 11:16.209
OH!

11:16.242 --> 11:18.778
I BELIEVE
I OWE YOU A PHONE CALL.

11:18.812 --> 11:22.248
MM-HMM. AND I BELIEVE
I OWE YOU THIS.

11:27.921 --> 11:30.123
LAST I KNOW, YOU'RE GOING TO
DALLAS TO WORK FOR MARK CUBAN.

11:30.890 --> 11:31.758
YOU DON'T
SAY GOODBYE TO ME.

11:32.892 --> 11:34.894
YOU DON'T ANSWER MY CALLS.
YOU DON'T ANSWER MY TEXTS.

11:34.928 --> 11:37.964
YOU JUST VANISH
DOWN SOME NICO RABBIT HOLE,

11:37.997 --> 11:41.067
AND THEN YOU POP UP LIKE
A FREAKING JACK-IN-THE-BOX

11:41.101 --> 11:44.304
ASKING FOR MY HELP,
AND FOR A PATIENT?

11:44.337 --> 11:47.307
I APOLOGIZE
FOR FALLING OUT OF TOUCH.

11:47.340 --> 11:48.942
WHERE THE HELL
HAVE YOU BEEN?

11:48.975 --> 11:50.243
HERE.

11:50.276 --> 11:51.845
YOU WORK HERE?
MM-HMM.

11:51.878 --> 11:53.913
EXPLAIN THAT.
IT'S COMPLICATED.

11:53.947 --> 11:57.350
YEAH, LET ME REPEAT MYSELF --
I THOUGHT YOU WERE DEAD.

11:57.384 --> 11:58.852
I SPENT MONTHS
WORRYING ABOUT YOU,

11:58.885 --> 12:00.987
LOSING SLEEP OVER YOU,

12:01.021 --> 12:02.222
AND THEN I COME TO FIND OUT
THAT YOU'RE JUST --

12:02.255 --> 12:06.026
YOU'RE HERE, WORKING
IN NEW YORK, SECURITY.

12:06.059 --> 12:09.829
YOU REALLY DO KNOW HOW
TO TORTURE PEOPLE, DON'T YOU?

12:09.863 --> 12:09.896
CONNOR WANTED ME TO MAKE
AN INTRODUCTION, SO I DID.

12:14.267 --> 12:17.771
I HEARD IT WASN'T WORKING OUT
SO WELL WITH THE HAWKS.

12:18.605 --> 12:20.373
I'M SORRY.

12:20.407 --> 12:23.009
I'LL BET YOU'RE SORRY.

12:23.043 --> 12:24.377
THERE YOU ARE. DR. SANTINO,
CAR'S READY FOR YOU.

12:24.411 --> 12:26.312
MM-HMM.
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

12:26.346 --> 12:28.048
AH, GOT TO TAKE THIS.

12:37.891 --> 12:42.362
* STANDING ON A RAIN CLOUD,
LOOKING DOWN ON THE WORLD *

12:42.395 --> 12:49.969
* ALL THE ROCK-'N'-ROLL BOYS
AND THEIR ROCK-'N'-ROLL GIRLS *

12:50.003 --> 12:52.839
* BLOOD RUNS RED

12:52.872 --> 12:54.841
* SKY GOES BLACK

12:54.874 --> 12:56.943
THAT'S DARRYL HUTCHINSON.

12:56.976 --> 12:58.044
HIS FRIENDS
CALL HIM ZEUS

12:58.078 --> 12:59.412
'CAUSE HE THROWS
LIGHTNING BOLTS.

12:59.446 --> 13:01.981
AND V3 ACADEMY
IS A BOARDING SCHOOL

13:02.015 --> 13:03.083
FOR STUDENT-ATHLETES.

13:03.116 --> 13:04.884
ELITE STUDENT-ATHLETES.

13:04.918 --> 13:06.986
WE GIVE THEM
THAT COMPETITIVE EDGE --

13:07.020 --> 13:08.388
BEST TRAINING,
BEST FACILITIES.

13:08.421 --> 13:10.924
WE TAKE STUDENTS
AND TURN THEM INTO SUPERSTARS.

13:10.957 --> 13:12.392
YOU GET AHOLD
OF THEM YOUNG, HUH?

13:12.425 --> 13:14.194
OH, DON'T TELL ME
YOU'RE A CYNIC THERE?

13:14.227 --> 13:15.862
JUST FROM NEW YORK.

13:15.895 --> 13:17.397
IT GOES
WITH THE TERRITORY.
UH-HUH.

13:17.430 --> 13:21.634
SO, KANSAS CITY, HUH?
IS THAT WHERE HE WANTS TO GO?

13:21.668 --> 13:23.169
WELL, NOT REALLY, AND I'D RATHER
HIM BE IN NEW YORK,

13:23.203 --> 13:24.938
BUT YOU GOT TO GO
WHERE YOU'RE DRAFTED.

13:24.971 --> 13:27.173
K.C. HAS THE NUMBER-ONE
DRAFT PICK THIS YEAR.
MM.

13:27.207 --> 13:28.341
YO, "HUTCH"!

13:28.375 --> 13:31.277
HEY, CONNOR.

13:31.311 --> 13:34.381
YOU SEE THAT LAST PITCH?
GUN HAD ME AT 101.

13:34.414 --> 13:36.383
WELL, OBVIOUSLY THERE'S
SOMETHING WRONG WITH THE GUN.

13:36.416 --> 13:37.951
NO ONE PITCHES
THAT FAST.

13:37.984 --> 13:38.952
OH, YEAH?
OW!

13:38.985 --> 13:40.387
HAVE YOU MET ME?
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

13:40.420 --> 13:41.955
DR. SANTINO,
THIS IS HUTCH.

13:41.988 --> 13:43.890
THIS IS THE WOMAN
I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT.

13:43.923 --> 13:45.425
SHRINK LADY, RIGHT?

13:45.458 --> 13:48.361
[ SIGHS ]
IT STARTED ABOUT A YEAR AGO.

13:48.395 --> 13:50.163
I WAS ON A FLIGHT HOME
TO ARIZONA,

13:50.196 --> 13:52.165
HIT SOME
REAL BAD TURBULENCE.

13:52.198 --> 13:53.967
[ SIGHS ]

13:54.000 --> 13:55.468
NOBODY WAS HURT,
BUT IT WAS TERRIFYING.

13:55.502 --> 13:59.039
HAVE YOU FLOWN SINCE?
YEAH.

13:59.072 --> 14:00.940
AT FIRST, I WASN'T HAVING
FULL-ON FREAK-OUTS,

14:00.974 --> 14:03.243
BUT IT'S BEEN GETTING
WORSE AND WORSE.

14:03.276 --> 14:06.046
LAST TIME, MY HEART WAS POUNDING
LIKE A JACKHAMMER.

14:06.079 --> 14:08.014
I THOUGHT I WAS HAVING
A HEART ATTACK.

14:08.682 --> 14:12.919
WELL, WITH THE DRAFT COMING UP
AND ALL THIS MONEY AT STAKE,

14:12.952 --> 14:15.188
THAT'S A LOT
FOR AN 18-YEAR-OLD.

14:15.221 --> 14:15.288
IF BASEBALL PAYS ME A LOT
OF DOUGH, THAT'S AWESOME,

14:18.992 --> 14:20.960
BUT I'M IN IT
BECAUSE I LOVE THE GAME.

14:20.994 --> 14:25.398
THE MOUND IS THE --
IT'S THE ONE PLACE I FEEL HAPPY.

14:25.432 --> 14:29.069
ARE YOU HAPPY HERE,
AT THE ACADEMY, AWAY FROM HOME?

14:29.102 --> 14:31.171
YOU KIDDING?

14:31.204 --> 14:33.373
IT'S THE GREATEST THING
THAT HAPPENED TO ME.

14:33.406 --> 14:35.508
I'VE SPENT FOUR YEARS
AT V3.

14:35.542 --> 14:37.143
CONNOR AND TROY
HAVE GIVEN ME

14:37.177 --> 14:39.012
EVERYTHING I NEED
TO REACH THE DREAM,

14:39.045 --> 14:41.281
AND NOW I'M GONNA BLOW IT
OVER SOMETHING THIS STUPID.

14:41.314 --> 14:46.019
HEY, HUTCH, FEAR OF FLYING
IS NOT AN UNCOMMON PHOBIA.

14:46.052 --> 14:49.122
AND LUCKILY, IT'S ONE
OF THE EASIEST TO TACKLE...

14:49.155 --> 14:51.991
IF YOU'RE MOTIVATED.

14:52.025 --> 14:53.993
HAVE YOU MET ME?

14:54.027 --> 14:55.195
GOOD.

14:55.228 --> 14:57.063
SO, THEN WE ARE GONNA
FACE THIS HEAD-ON.

14:57.097 --> 15:00.400
WE'RE GONNA GET YOU ON THAT
PLANE TO KANSAS CITY -- PYOW!

15:00.433 --> 15:03.403
BUT FIRST,
WE'RE GONNA DO A DRY RUN.

15:03.436 --> 15:04.971
I UNDERSTAND THAT
YOU HAVE TO BE IN PHILLY

15:05.005 --> 15:06.306
FOR AN INTERVIEW,
RIGHT?

15:06.339 --> 15:09.042
YEAH. WITH SOME REPORTERS,
THURSDAY.

15:09.075 --> 15:10.076
EXCELLENT.

15:10.110 --> 15:12.946
THEN WE HAVE TIME
FOR A FEW SESSIONS BEFOREHAND.

15:14.347 --> 15:17.250
SO, THE INTERNATIONAL
MAN OF MYSTERY RETURNS,

15:17.283 --> 15:18.351
AND YOU WHACK HIM.

15:18.385 --> 15:20.453
THAT IS SO
"FIFTY SHADES."

15:20.487 --> 15:23.289
DID HE TAKE YOU INTO HIS ARMS
AND THROW YOU UP AGAINST A WALL?

15:23.323 --> 15:26.192
NO. I SHOULD HAVE THROWN HIM
UP AGAINST THE WALL.

15:26.226 --> 15:27.761
I MEAN, HE'S MAKING ME SWEAT
ALL THOSE MONTHS,

15:27.794 --> 15:30.397
AND THE WHOLE TIME,
HE'S ONLY WORKING A BRIDGE
AND TUNNEL AWAY?

15:30.430 --> 15:33.566
WHAT KIND OF PERSON DOES THAT
TO A...A FRIEND?

15:33.600 --> 15:36.136
MAYBE YOU BROKE
HIS HEART,

15:36.169 --> 15:39.005
AND SEEING YOU WAS TOO MUCH
FOR HIM TO BEAR.

15:39.039 --> 15:40.040
YOU'RE NOT
ACTUALLY READING

15:40.940 --> 15:41.441
THAT "FIFTY SHADES"
OF PORNO, ARE YOU?

15:42.242 --> 15:42.542
WHAT DO YOU THINK
GOT ME THROUGH

15:43.309 --> 15:44.210
ALL THOSE SLEEPLESS
BABY NIGHTS?

15:44.911 --> 15:46.579
HMM.
DON'T BE TOO MAD AT HIM.

15:46.613 --> 15:48.281
HE DID GET YOU
THIS GIG.

15:48.314 --> 15:50.216
AND I WILL BE GLAD
WHEN IT'S DONE.

15:50.250 --> 15:51.785
AFTER WHAT
HE PUT ME THROUGH,

15:51.818 --> 15:55.221
I NEVER WANT TO SEE
"SIR SNEAKO" EVER AGAIN.

15:55.255 --> 15:58.425
I KNOW HOW THIS ENDS --
HATE SEX.

15:58.458 --> 16:01.394
IT'S THE BEST WORST KIND.

16:01.428 --> 16:02.529
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:02.562 --> 16:05.532
* RIGHT, RIGHT,
RIGHT, RIGHT, RIGHT *

16:07.167 --> 16:11.504
* RIGHT, RIGHT,
RIGHT, RIGHT, RIGHT *

16:11.538 --> 16:13.073
OKAY, WHY CAN'T WE
JUST DRIVE?

16:14.107 --> 16:14.140
I MEAN, WE CAN GET THERE
IN LIKE AN HOUR AND A HALF.

16:15.075 --> 16:16.109
IT'S PHILLY.
IT'S JUST A 30-MINUTE FLIGHT.

16:17.243 --> 16:19.346
WE'RE GETTING ON THE PLANE,
BUT WE WON'T CLOSE THE DOOR,

16:19.379 --> 16:19.412
AND WE WON'T TAKE OFF
UNLESS YOU SAY YOU'RE READY.

16:21.247 --> 16:22.582
[ PLANE ENGINE ROARS ]

16:22.615 --> 16:24.117
LOOK AT ME.

16:24.150 --> 16:26.052
LOOK AT ME -- DARRYL.
LISTEN.

16:26.086 --> 16:29.356
YOU'VE HEARD THAT EXPRESSION
"KEEP YOUR EYE ON THE BALL?"

16:29.389 --> 16:32.258
WELL, RIGHT NOW
THE BALL IS KANSAS CITY.

16:32.292 --> 16:34.461
THIS IS THE FIRST STEP
IN GETTING YOU THERE.

16:34.494 --> 16:37.230
THOSE STAIRS
TAKE YOU TO YOUR DREAM...

16:37.263 --> 16:40.400
BUT YOU NEED TO DECIDE
HOW BADLY YOU WANT IT.

16:45.705 --> 16:48.074
I CAN'T BREATHE.
I FEEL LIKE I HAVE --

16:48.808 --> 16:49.442
I HAVE A BOULDER
ON MY CHEST.

16:50.210 --> 16:51.778
I'M SWEATING.
I FEEL LIGHT-HEADED.

16:51.811 --> 16:54.214
I'M GONNA THROW UP.
I'M GONNA...
OKAY.

16:54.247 --> 16:57.784
LOOK AT ME.
SEE HOW CALM I AM?

16:57.817 --> 16:59.786
I WANT YOU TO REPEAT
AFTER ME --

16:59.819 --> 17:03.490
"THIS IS A SAFE
AND EASY WAY TO TRAVEL."

17:03.523 --> 17:07.794
THIS IS A SAFE
AND EASY WAY TO TRAVEL.

17:07.827 --> 17:09.229
AGAIN.

17:09.262 --> 17:11.831
THIS IS A SAFE
AND EASY WAY TO TRAVEL.

17:11.865 --> 17:14.768
WE HAVE BEEN SITTING HERE
FOR 20 MINUTES.

17:14.801 --> 17:16.269
WHAT DO YOU THINK
OUR ODDS

17:16.302 --> 17:17.871
THAT THIS PLANE'S
EVER GONNA TAKE OFF?

17:17.904 --> 17:21.441
WELL, IF THIS WAS VEGAS,
I'D BET AGAINST YOU.

17:21.474 --> 17:23.543
BUT IT'S NOT.

17:23.576 --> 17:25.245
Darryl: NO, THIS IS NOT --
I CAN'T -- I CAN'T -- NO! NO!

17:25.278 --> 17:26.513
OH, OH, OH, OH! OH!

17:27.514 --> 17:30.150
I AM GOING TO GIVE YOU
SOMETHING TO CALM YOU DOWN.

17:30.183 --> 17:33.153
THIS MEDICINE
HAS NO SIDE EFFECTS

17:33.186 --> 17:33.920
AND IT KICKS IN
IMMEDIATELY.

17:34.721 --> 17:36.189
WHAT --
WHAT IS SHE GIVING HIM?

17:36.923 --> 17:38.792
LET IT PLAY OUT.
SHE KNOWS WHAT SHE'S DOING.

17:38.825 --> 17:41.761
DON'T I NEED PERMISSION
TO TAKE MEDS?
ALREADY GOT IT.

17:41.795 --> 17:43.563
OKAY, OKAY.

17:43.596 --> 17:45.165
ALL RIGHT.

17:47.867 --> 17:51.571
YOU'RE GOING TO START TO FEEL
CALM ALMOST IMMEDIATELY.

17:51.604 --> 17:54.841
YOUR BREATHING
WILL SLOW,

17:54.874 --> 17:57.644
YOUR MUSCLES
WILL UNCLENCH,

17:57.677 --> 18:02.482
AND YOU WILL SUDDENLY REALIZE
THAT EVERYTHING'S OKAY.

18:02.515 --> 18:05.485
OW. [ CHUCKLES ]

18:05.518 --> 18:08.221
PITCHERS
HAVE STRONG GRIPS.

18:08.254 --> 18:12.192
SORRY. I, UH -- I THOUGHT
MY BALL GOT THE WORST OF IT.

18:12.225 --> 18:13.293
IT'S OKAY.

18:14.361 --> 18:15.595
BUT THAT PILL SHOULD BE
KICKING IN RIGHT ABOUT NOW,

18:15.628 --> 18:18.164
SO YOU JUST
SAY THE WORD.

18:20.233 --> 18:22.268
CLOSE THE DOOR.

18:23.670 --> 18:25.605
YOU CAN CLOSE THE DOOR.

18:27.741 --> 18:28.875
[ SIGHS ]

18:28.908 --> 18:30.543
MAN, THESE PILLS
ARE AWESOME.

18:30.577 --> 18:31.644
UH-HUH.

18:31.678 --> 18:33.279
WHAT ARE THEY?

18:33.313 --> 18:34.814
SKITTLES.

18:34.848 --> 18:37.517
IT'S CALLED
THE PLACEBO EFFECT.

18:37.550 --> 18:40.887
FEAR OF FLYING
IS ALL IN YOUR HEAD,

18:40.920 --> 18:43.890
AND I WANTED TO SHOW YOU
HOW POWERFUL YOUR MIND CAN BE.

18:43.923 --> 18:47.327
YOU CAN CALM YOURSELF DOWN
ANYTIME YOU WANT.

18:48.795 --> 18:50.230
Dr. McTavish: A ZOMBIE?

18:50.263 --> 18:53.233
YEAH.

18:53.266 --> 18:54.934
I THINK I'M
A FLESH-EATING ZOMBIE.

18:54.968 --> 18:56.903
HOW LONG HAVE
YOU HAD THESE FEELINGS?

18:56.936 --> 19:00.206
EVER SINCE I WAS BITTEN BY
THAT OTHER FLESH-EATING ZOMBIE.

19:00.240 --> 19:01.908
[ LAUGHS ]

19:04.778 --> 19:06.713
THAT WAS A JOKE.

19:06.746 --> 19:09.582
[ Chuckling ] YOUR --
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:13.586 --> 19:16.823
DON'T THERAPISTS
NORMALLY HAVE A COUCH?

19:16.856 --> 19:18.625
SOME.

19:18.658 --> 19:20.360
AND DON'T THEY NORMALLY
HAVE, LIKE, YOU KNOW,

19:20.393 --> 19:25.398
SNACKS AND NIBLETS THAT
THEIR PATIENTS CAN PARTAKE IN?

19:25.432 --> 19:27.267
SOME.

19:27.300 --> 19:28.835
[ PEN SCRATCHING ]

19:30.704 --> 19:32.772
WHAT ARE YOU WRITING
IN YOUR LITTLE PAD THERE?

19:32.806 --> 19:35.275
DETAILS
I LIKE TO REMEMBER.

19:35.308 --> 19:37.844
OH. GETTING THE SCOOP THERE,
HUH, WOLF BLITZER?

19:37.877 --> 19:39.579
THAT'S HOW
THE UNABOMBER STARTED.

19:39.612 --> 19:41.348
GOT HIMSELF A LITTLE PEN,
A LITTLE PAD,

19:41.381 --> 19:43.650
STARTED WRITING DOWN STUFF
HE WANTED TO REMEMBER.

19:43.683 --> 19:45.418
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT HE WANTED TO REMEMBER?

19:45.452 --> 19:46.886
BUILDINGS,
SO HE COULD BLOW THEM UP.

19:57.430 --> 20:02.268
"DOUBLE WINDSOR KNOT.
WAY TOO FAT FOR HIS FRAME."

20:02.302 --> 20:04.637
* DO-DO, DO-DO, DO-DO

20:04.671 --> 20:08.008
"AND STILL HAS A PRICE TAG
ON HIS PANTS."

20:08.041 --> 20:09.709
CUTE. YOU STOLE THOSE.

20:09.743 --> 20:10.844
[ SCOFFS ]

20:10.877 --> 20:14.881
TERRENCE, WOULD YOU LIKE FOR ME
TO PUT THE PAD DOWN?

20:17.083 --> 20:19.319
THAT'S MY WHOLE DAMN POINT,
HOMEBOY.

20:19.352 --> 20:21.721
I DON'T SEE WHY YOU NEED A PAD.
DR. D NEVER WROTE ANYTHING DOWN.

20:21.755 --> 20:24.824
SHE REMEMBERED EVERYTHING I SAID
BECAUSE IT WAS IMPORTANT TO HER,

20:24.858 --> 20:26.426
PLUS,
SHE HAD A SOFA, OKAY?

20:26.459 --> 20:27.794
WITH SOME
COMFY-ASS PILLOWS.

20:27.827 --> 20:29.696
I DON'T MEAN "ASS PILLOWS."
I MEAN...

20:29.729 --> 20:30.997
THIS --
THIS IS A WASTE OF TIME.

20:31.031 --> 20:31.898
YOU KNOW WHAT?
AND YOURS.

20:31.931 --> 20:34.000
TERRENCE, IS THERE SOMETHING
I CAN GET YOU

20:34.034 --> 20:35.735
THAT WOULD MAKE YOU
MORE COMFORTABLE?

20:37.804 --> 20:41.041
YEAH...
SOME JELLY BEANS.

20:43.710 --> 20:45.745
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

20:48.448 --> 20:50.717
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

20:50.750 --> 20:52.385
WE'RE GONNA
PLAY "20 QUESTIONS."

20:52.419 --> 20:54.020
HOW COME YOU DIDN'T GO
TO DALLAS?

20:54.054 --> 20:55.722
CHANGE OF PLANS.
YEAH, BUT WHY?

20:55.755 --> 20:56.990
AND HOW COME
YOU DIDN'T CALL ME BACK?

20:57.023 --> 20:58.658
AND WHAT, ARE WE BACK
TO ONE-WORD ANSWERS

20:58.692 --> 20:59.726
LIKE "PITTSBURGH"?

20:59.759 --> 21:01.461
MM.
THAT'S THREE QUESTIONS.

21:01.494 --> 21:02.896
AND NO ANSWERS.

21:02.929 --> 21:04.030
ARE YOU GONNA
SLAP ME AGAIN?

21:04.064 --> 21:06.800
NO...
BUT I'D LIKE TO.

21:08.034 --> 21:09.469
Pilot:
<i>LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,</i>

21:10.603 --> 21:11.371
<i>PLEASE RETURN YOUR SEATS</i>
<i>TO THEIR UPRIGHT POSITION.</i>

21:12.572 --> 21:13.073
<i>WE'LL BE STARTING OUR DESCENT</i>
<i>IN JUST A FEW MOMENTS.</i>

21:13.873 --> 21:14.407
YOU BETTER GET BACK
TO YOUR SEAT.

21:15.041 --> 21:16.943
YOU'RE NOT
OFF THE HOOK.

21:28.121 --> 21:31.725
[ BASEBALL THUDS ]

21:31.758 --> 21:33.960
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

21:36.730 --> 21:38.498
WHERE ARE WE?

21:38.531 --> 21:39.866
WE'RE IN PHILLY. YOU DID IT.
YOU'RE OKAY.

21:43.169 --> 21:44.971
NO, I'M NOT.

21:45.005 --> 21:46.506
HUTCH?

21:46.539 --> 21:48.775
HEY, TALK TO ME.
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

21:48.808 --> 21:50.810
MY ARM'S NUMB.

21:50.844 --> 21:53.380
HEY. OKAY.
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

21:53.413 --> 21:56.116
LOOK I -- I CAN'T --
I CANNOT FEEL MY ARM!

22:02.589 --> 22:03.990
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THIS SHOWS?

22:04.691 --> 22:05.125
I'M NOT
A MEDICAL DOCTOR.

22:05.792 --> 22:07.027
WELL,
THAT MUCH IS CLEAR.

22:07.060 --> 22:08.661
I WILL TELL YOU
WHAT IT SHOWS.

22:08.695 --> 22:09.863
IT SHOWS THAT NOTHING

22:10.730 --> 22:11.064
IS PHYSICALLY WRONG
WITH HUTCH'S ARM

22:12.065 --> 22:12.098
AND NOTHING WAS WRONG
WITH HIS ARM -- PERIOD --

22:12.999 --> 22:15.135
UNTIL YOU TALKED TO HIM. SO...
[ SIGHS ]

22:15.168 --> 22:17.037
WHAT THE HELL
DID YOU SAY TO HIM?

22:17.070 --> 22:19.706
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT DID I<i>SAY?</i>
YEAH.

22:19.739 --> 22:21.574
THE KID THROWS LIKE KOUFAX,
AND THEN HE TALKS TO YOU,

22:21.608 --> 22:21.641
AND HE'S GOT MUPPET ARM.
WHAT DID YOU SAY?
[ SIGHS ]

22:23.710 --> 22:25.011
FIRSTLY...

22:25.045 --> 22:27.113
MY CONVERSATIONS
WITH HUTCH ARE CONFIDENTIAL.

22:27.147 --> 22:31.117
AND SECONDLY, NOTHING I SAY
CAN MAKE HIS ARM GO NUMB.

22:31.151 --> 22:32.952
Connor: ALL RIGHT,
WE GOT A KID WHO WON'T FLY,

22:32.986 --> 22:33.720
AND NOW HE CAN'T PITCH.

22:33.753 --> 22:35.155
HE'S GOT TO BE ON --
AND OFF --

22:35.188 --> 22:37.457
THAT PLANE
IN KANSAS CITY IN FIVE DAYS.

22:37.490 --> 22:38.725
WHAT NOW?

22:38.758 --> 22:40.126
I THINK
THAT HUTCH IS SUFFERING

22:40.160 --> 22:42.429
FROM A SORT
OF CONVERSION DISORDER --

22:42.462 --> 22:43.997
A PSYCHOSOMATIC ILLNESS.

22:44.030 --> 22:45.632
IT STARTED
WITH THE FEAR OF FLYING,

22:45.665 --> 22:47.634
THEN IT BECAME
ABOUT THE NUMBNESS IN THE ARM,

22:47.667 --> 22:50.570
AND IT MIGHT EVENTUALLY BECOME
ABOUT SOMETHING ELSE ENTIRELY.

22:50.603 --> 22:52.005
SO, HE'S MAKING IT UP?

22:52.038 --> 22:55.141
OH, NO.
IT'S VERY REAL TO HIM.

22:55.175 --> 22:58.111
ALL RIGHT, WHAT COULD CAUSE
THIS CONVERSION DISORDER?

22:58.144 --> 23:00.980
IT'S USUALLY TRIGGERED
BY SOME EXTERNAL STRESSORS.
MM.

23:01.014 --> 23:03.083
I'D LIKE TO SEE
HIS MEDICAL RECORDS.

23:03.116 --> 23:04.617
OH, SO NOW
OH, SO NOW
<i>A</i>A MEDICAL DOCTOR?

23:04.651 --> 23:06.152
I'M SORRY.
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

23:06.186 --> 23:07.554
YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHAT'S RIDICULOUS?

23:08.755 --> 23:08.788
BRINGING ME INTO A FIGHT WITH
ONE HAND TIED BEHIND MY BACK.

23:09.723 --> 23:11.624
I HAPPEN TO KNOW MY WAY
AROUND TWO THINGS --

23:11.658 --> 23:13.560
MENTAL HEALTH
AND SICILIAN COOKING.

23:13.593 --> 23:14.761
SO WHY DON'T YOU HELP ME
HELP YOUR CLIENT,

23:14.794 --> 23:16.563
OR ELSE LET ME GO HOME
AND COOK SOME LASAGNA

23:16.596 --> 23:18.665
WHERE PEOPLE
ARE NOT SECOND-GUESSING ME

23:18.698 --> 23:20.734
AT EVERY TURN?

23:20.767 --> 23:23.603
ALL RIGHT, NICO,
WILL YOU GIVE DR. SANTINO

23:23.636 --> 23:25.939
HUTCH'S MEDICAL RECORDS,
PLEASE?

23:25.972 --> 23:27.941
SURE THING.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

23:29.609 --> 23:32.178
WE DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR A FISHING EXPEDITION.

23:32.212 --> 23:34.581
WE BROUGHT ON DR. SANTINO
TO DO A JOB.

23:34.614 --> 23:36.049
LET'S LET HER DO IT.

23:36.082 --> 23:38.651
QUITE FRANKLY,
WE'RE OUT OF OPTIONS.

23:43.023 --> 23:44.157
THERE'S A GAP.

23:44.190 --> 23:46.059
WHAT KIND OF GAP?

23:46.092 --> 23:48.661
IN YOUR ATTENDANCE RECORD --
I NOTICED THAT YOU WERE ABSENT

23:48.695 --> 23:51.998
FOR TWO WEEKS
FROM SCHOOL LAST JUNE.

23:52.032 --> 23:52.999
DO YOU REMEMBER THAT?

23:53.033 --> 23:54.634
KIND OF.
I HAD SOME BUG.

23:54.668 --> 23:57.203
WHAT KIND OF BUG?

23:57.237 --> 23:58.772
I DON'T KNOW.

23:59.973 --> 24:02.776
THEY THOUGHT I HAD MONO,
BUT TESTS WERE NEGATIVE.

24:02.809 --> 24:07.013
WHAT'S THIS GOT TO DO WITH
FLYING, WITH MY ARM GOING NUMB?

24:07.047 --> 24:08.548
OH, I'M JUST
TRYING TO PIECE TOGETHER

24:08.581 --> 24:10.684
WHETHER OR NOT YOU'VE HAD
BOUTS OF THIS BEFORE.

24:10.717 --> 24:12.519
IF YOU'RE ASKING WHEN
I FIRST BECAME A BASKET CASE,

24:12.552 --> 24:13.720
I DON'T KNOW,
ALL RIGHT?

24:14.854 --> 24:14.888
ALL I KNOW IS THAT I WAS
FLINGING 100 MILES AN HOUR.

24:16.089 --> 24:18.792
NOW I'M BARELY CLEARING 70.
HOW IS THAT ALL IN MY HEAD?

24:18.825 --> 24:20.260
BEING A FIRST-ROUND
DRAFT PICK --

24:20.293 --> 24:22.028
THAT'S GOT TO BE
A LOT OF PRESSURE.

24:22.062 --> 24:24.564
[ Chuckling ]
LOOK, I TOSSED A SHUTOUT

24:24.597 --> 24:26.566
IN THE LITTLE LEAGUE
WORLD SERIES WHEN I WAS 12.

24:26.599 --> 24:29.102
I HAVE HAD SCOUTS
POKING AROUND SINCE I WAS 14.

24:29.135 --> 24:31.805
I MEAN, PRESSURE --
IT'S NEVER BOTHERED ME BEFORE.

24:31.838 --> 24:33.039
I EAT PRESSURE FOR BREAKFAST,
YOU KNOW?

24:33.973 --> 24:36.843
WE TALKED ABOUT
HOW POWERFUL YOUR MIND IS.

24:36.876 --> 24:39.245
WELL, YOURS
IS SABOTAGING YOU...

24:39.279 --> 24:43.049
FOR A REASON.

24:44.784 --> 24:47.721
ALL OF MY DREAMS
ARE ABOUT TO COME TRUE.

24:49.255 --> 24:51.758
WHY THE HELL
WOULDN'T I WANT THAT?

24:59.766 --> 25:03.737
NONSPECIFIC VIRUS?

25:03.770 --> 25:07.307
THIS WHOLE CASE
IS A NONSPECIFIC VIRUS.

25:07.340 --> 25:08.575
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

25:25.725 --> 25:28.328
OH.

25:32.365 --> 25:33.733
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

25:33.767 --> 25:34.834
[ GRUNTING ]

25:34.868 --> 25:36.636
Man: COME ON, LADIES!

25:36.670 --> 25:38.638
Man #2: ONE MORE.
THAT'S IT, MAN. YOU CAN DO IT.

25:38.672 --> 25:42.342
* OH, YEAH

25:42.375 --> 25:46.780
HEY, LARSON, DON'T YOU
MAKE A MESS ON MY FIELD.

25:46.813 --> 25:49.215
COACH, I REALLY DON'T FEEL LIKE
CALLING AN AMBULANCE TODAY.

25:49.249 --> 25:49.315
THEY DON'T KNOW
WHAT SACRIFICE IS.

25:51.785 --> 25:54.654
UNTIL THEY DO, THEY'LL NEVER WIN
THE GAME THAT REALLY MATTERS.

25:54.688 --> 25:56.322
LARSON, YOU GOOD?
Larson: YEAH.

25:56.356 --> 25:59.926
GET HIM SOME FLUIDS,
AND GET HIS ASS BACK OUT HERE.

25:59.959 --> 26:01.127
MR. KING!

26:01.161 --> 26:02.862
BECAUSE YOU STOPPED,

26:02.896 --> 26:05.632
EVERYONE HERE IS GONNA RUN
UNTIL I GET TIRED.

26:05.665 --> 26:07.367
AGAIN!

26:07.400 --> 26:09.135
WHAT?!
THAT'S RIDICULOUS!

26:09.169 --> 26:11.671
AND THAT
JUST COST YOU $1,000.

26:11.705 --> 26:13.673
HE'S STROKING OVER HERE, COACH.
WE ALL ARE.

26:13.707 --> 26:16.209
ARE YOU TRYING
TO KILL THE TEAM?
AND THAT'S ANOTHER $1,000.

26:16.242 --> 26:18.378
EVERY SINGLE WORD
THAT COMES OUT OF YOUR MOUTH

26:18.411 --> 26:19.879
IS ANOTHER $1,000.

26:19.913 --> 26:22.215
WELL, I'M DONE TALKING,
HOMEBOY. HOW ABOUT THAT?

26:22.248 --> 26:25.719
SCREW YOU, SCREW THE HAWKS.
AND SCREW YOUR RULES.
"T"...

26:25.752 --> 26:26.853
I QUIT.

26:28.421 --> 26:30.223
KEEP IT GOING!

26:30.256 --> 26:32.359
IT'S FOURTH QUARTER.
THAT'S WHEN IT COUNTS.

26:32.392 --> 26:33.226
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

26:33.259 --> 26:35.228
ABOUT TO GET CHINESE FOOD
IN YONKERS.

26:35.261 --> 26:36.296
YOU WANT TO COME?
STOP IT.

26:37.263 --> 26:39.199
AFTER EVERYTHING
THAT YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH?

26:39.232 --> 26:40.400
YOU'RE THROWING AWAY
A CHANCE

26:40.433 --> 26:42.202
TO WORK WITH
THE BEST COACH IN FOOTBALL?

26:42.235 --> 26:43.737
[ LAUGHS ]
[ ALARM CHIRPS ]

26:43.770 --> 26:45.405
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA
GET THIS CHANCE AGAIN.

26:45.438 --> 26:46.840
HELL,
YOU LEAVE LIKE THIS,

26:48.041 --> 26:51.845
YOU MAY NEVER GET YOUR SHOT
IN THE<i>LEAGUE</i>AGAIN.

26:51.878 --> 26:53.346
YOU DIDN'T EVEN
FIGHT FOR HER.

26:53.380 --> 26:54.414
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

26:54.447 --> 26:55.882
DR. D.

26:55.915 --> 26:57.951
SHE SAVED MY ASS.

26:57.984 --> 26:59.319
SHE SAVED<i>YOUR</i>ASS.

26:59.352 --> 27:01.855
SHE SAVED THIS ENTIRE TEAM'S
COLLECTIVE ASS,

27:01.888 --> 27:03.390
AND ALL YOU DID
WAS WIPE HER AND FLUSH HER.

27:03.423 --> 27:07.861
TERRENCE, I'M SORRY
THAT SHE'S GONE.

27:07.894 --> 27:08.862
RIGHT. RIGHT.

27:08.895 --> 27:10.463
RIGHT. RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT?

27:10.497 --> 27:12.365
"T," COME ON. YOU'VE BEEN
IN THIS GAME LONG ENOUGH.

27:12.399 --> 27:13.433
YOU KNOW.

27:14.434 --> 27:15.969
PLAYERS, COACHES,
EXECUTIVES, THERAPISTS --

27:16.002 --> 27:18.304
THEY COME AND GO.

27:19.906 --> 27:26.179
YEAH, WELL, HE CAME,
SHE GOES, I'M GONE.

27:29.883 --> 27:30.884
Nico: CRABCHEK?

27:30.917 --> 27:32.252
YES,
JUNE OF LAST YEAR,

27:33.319 --> 27:34.354
THERE WAS A KID AT THE ACADEMY
NAMED JOSEPH CRABCHEK

27:35.088 --> 27:35.889
WHO WITHDREW
FROM THE DRAFT.

27:35.922 --> 27:37.023
AND?

27:37.057 --> 27:39.025
AND THERE WAS
NEVER ANY MENTION

27:39.059 --> 27:41.027
WHY HE LEFT OR HOW HE LEFT
IN THE PRESS.

27:41.061 --> 27:43.396
SO I'M THINKING THAT MAYBE
IT'S THE MISSING PIECE.

27:43.430 --> 27:45.031
DID YOU ASK TROY
OR CONNOR?

27:45.065 --> 27:47.801
NO, I WAS HOPING
THAT I WOULDN'T HAVE TO.

27:47.834 --> 27:49.302
HEY. LISTEN.

27:49.336 --> 27:53.239
CAN YOU STOP BEING NICO
FOR JUST A SECOND?

27:53.273 --> 27:55.442
YOU BROUGHT ME HERE
TO HELP THIS KID.

27:55.475 --> 27:57.344
I'M TELLING YOU
THERE'S A MISSING PIECE

27:57.377 --> 27:59.379
AND THAT I NEED<i>YOUR</i>HELP
TO FIGURE IT OUT.

27:59.412 --> 28:01.381
I'LL SEE
WHAT I CAN FIND OUT.

28:01.414 --> 28:03.383
OKAY.

28:04.351 --> 28:05.485
DANI...

28:07.253 --> 28:09.789
...IF I TOLD YOU IT WAS
FOR PERSONAL REASONS --

28:09.823 --> 28:11.758
NOT GOING TO DALLAS...

28:12.992 --> 28:15.362
...COULD YOU ACCEPT THAT?

28:17.864 --> 28:20.000
IF I HAVE TO.

28:20.033 --> 28:24.371
FOR THE RECORD,
I NEVER MEANT TO HURT YOU.

28:26.006 --> 28:28.375
DITTO.

28:32.846 --> 28:34.481
[ SIGHS ]

28:34.514 --> 28:36.349
HE QUIT?!

28:36.383 --> 28:38.018
DROVE OFF
IN THE MIDDLE OF PRACTICE.

28:38.051 --> 28:40.787
WOW. I'M SURE THAT WENT OVER
REALLY WELL WITH THE COACH.

28:40.820 --> 28:43.256
LOOK. IT'S PROBABLY TOO LATE,
BUT YOU GOT TO DO SOMETHING.

28:43.289 --> 28:45.325
ALL RIGHT? YOU'RE THE ONLY
PERSON HE'S GONNA LISTEN TO.

28:45.358 --> 28:47.460
HAVE YOU FORGOTTEN
THAT THE HAWKS FIRED ME?

28:47.494 --> 28:48.528
HE'S NOT
MY CLIENT ANYMORE.

28:49.462 --> 28:50.463
HE JUST NEEDS SOMEONE
TO TALK HIM DOWN.

28:50.497 --> 28:53.466
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]
THE TEAM HAS A NEW THERAPIST.

28:53.500 --> 28:54.567
YOU'VE GOT HIM
ON SPEED DIAL.

28:54.601 --> 28:55.869
YOU CAN'T JUST
PICK UP THE PHONE?

28:55.902 --> 28:58.071
WHAT,
TO PUSH YOUR AGENDA?

28:58.104 --> 29:00.340
HE'S NOT MY FRIEND.
HE'S A FORMER CLIENT.

29:00.373 --> 29:01.541
THERE'S
ETHICAL ISSUES HERE.

29:01.574 --> 29:03.009
JESUS, DANI.

29:03.043 --> 29:05.278
YOU KNOW, YOU DIDN'T HAVE
A PROBLEM WITH MY RULES

29:05.311 --> 29:07.881
WHEN WE WERE
ON THE SAME TEAM.

29:09.382 --> 29:11.384
LOOK. I'M SORRY HOW THINGS
WENT DOWN, ALL RIGHT?

29:11.418 --> 29:13.520
WIZINSKI'S AN ASS.
NO ONE'S GONNA DENY IT.

29:13.553 --> 29:14.521
I'M SURE
THAT IF YOU WENT IN

29:14.554 --> 29:15.555
AND SAT DOWN
AND TALKED TO HIM --

29:16.456 --> 29:17.991
YOU MEAN APOLOGIZE TO HIM
ON BENDED KNEE

29:18.024 --> 29:19.459
AND MAYBE
I'LL GET MY JOB BACK?

29:19.492 --> 29:21.061
NO. OKAY?

29:21.094 --> 29:23.863
WE COULD MAKE NICE
FOR A DAY OR TWO.

29:23.897 --> 29:25.065
AND THEN,
ON THE THIRD DAY,

29:26.199 --> 29:29.102
WE WOULD BE HAVING THIS
CONVERSATION AGAIN -- AND AGAIN.

29:29.135 --> 29:31.004
LET'S FACE IT.

29:31.037 --> 29:34.307
MY TIME WITH THE HAWKS
IS OVER.

29:36.376 --> 29:38.978
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

29:42.582 --> 29:44.484
HEY.
MIND IF I COME IN?

29:44.517 --> 29:45.485
OH. OKAY.

29:45.518 --> 29:46.986
Matt: NICO.

29:47.020 --> 29:49.356
THOUGHT YOU WERE
IN DALLAS.

29:49.389 --> 29:51.091
UH, YEAH. IT DIDN'T PAN OUT.
I'M STILL IN TOWN.

29:51.124 --> 29:53.426
OH, WE HAVE
A CLIENT TOGETHER.

29:53.460 --> 29:57.163
HEARD YOU WERE HAVING A BABY.
CONGRATULATIONS.

29:57.197 --> 29:59.366
YEAH. THANKS.

30:00.934 --> 30:02.502
WELL, HEY.
THIS REUNION HAS BEEN FUN.

30:02.535 --> 30:05.138
[ CHUCKLES ] BUT I GOT TO
GET BACK AT IT.

30:05.171 --> 30:07.607
GOOD NIGHT.
SEE YOU GUYS.

30:07.640 --> 30:10.043
[ SIGHS ]

30:10.076 --> 30:12.912
I ASSUME THAT YOU HAVEN'T
COME HERE TO CHITTY-CHAT.

30:12.946 --> 30:16.149
I FOUND SOMETHING
I THOUGHT YOU'D LIKE TO SEE.

30:16.182 --> 30:19.419
A POLICE REPORT...
JOSEPH CRABCHEK.

30:19.452 --> 30:22.856
FROM JUNE OF LAST YEAR.
LOOK WHO THE WITNESS WAS.

30:27.093 --> 30:29.562
DARRYL HUTCHINSON.

30:38.138 --> 30:40.407
TELL ME
ABOUT JOSEPH CRABCHEK.

30:41.274 --> 30:43.977
JOE CRABCHEK?
HE'S ANCIENT HISTORY.

30:44.010 --> 30:46.079
WELL, HE MAY BE
A CURRENT EVENT, TOO.

30:46.112 --> 30:46.913
WHAT ARE YOU,
A TIME-TRAVELING THERAPIST?

30:46.946 --> 30:47.414
LEAVE IT ALONE.

30:47.981 --> 30:48.982
IF I COULD TIME TRAVEL,

30:49.015 --> 30:51.451
I WOULD GO BACK AND FIGURE OUT
WHO STOLE YOUR TOYS.

30:51.484 --> 30:52.652
WHAT'S WITH THE GAMES?
I DON'T --

30:52.686 --> 30:54.020
O-OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

30:54.054 --> 30:57.457
CAN YOU GRAB THE DOOR,
PLEASE?

30:58.558 --> 31:00.994
JOSEPH CRABCHEK
WAS A KID HERE AT V3

31:01.027 --> 31:02.996
WHO OPTED OUT
OF THE DRAFT LAST YEAR.

31:03.029 --> 31:04.531
YES,
I READ THOSE ARTICLES.

31:04.564 --> 31:06.466
ALL RIGHT, SO, WHAT'S THIS HAVE
TO DO WITH HUTCH'S ARM?

31:06.499 --> 31:08.201
I THINK EVERYTHING.

31:10.170 --> 31:13.006
Darryl: [ SIGHS ]
JOE CRABCHEK?

31:13.039 --> 31:15.141
WHAT ABOUT HIM?

31:15.175 --> 31:19.012
YOU TELL ME.
WHAT'S THERE TO KNOW?

31:20.280 --> 31:23.016
UH, HE WAS A YEAR AHEAD
OF ME AT THE ACADEMY.

31:23.049 --> 31:25.719
BESIDES JOE BEING
THE BEST PITCHER I EVER KNEW,

31:25.752 --> 31:27.654
HE WAS A STAND-UP GUY.

31:27.687 --> 31:29.556
SO, HE WAS WELL-LIKED.

31:29.589 --> 31:31.057
WELL-LIKED?

31:31.091 --> 31:34.561
[ CHUCKLES ]
LOOK. THE DUDE WAS A LEGEND.

31:34.594 --> 31:36.296
ALL THE PITCHERS
LOOKED UP TO HIM --

31:36.329 --> 31:38.164
TOUGH, FUNNY...

31:38.198 --> 31:41.267
HAD A WICKED-HARD SLIDER
NO ONE COULD HIT.

31:41.301 --> 31:43.536
HE WAS SET TO GO
EARLY IN THE FIRST ROUND.

31:43.570 --> 31:44.637
JUST LIKE YOU.

31:44.671 --> 31:47.107
YEAH.

31:47.140 --> 31:48.708
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM,
HUTCH?

31:48.742 --> 31:52.479
UH...

31:52.512 --> 31:55.582
ONE NIGHT...

31:55.615 --> 31:58.585
ABOUT A WEEK
BEFORE THE DRAFT, UH...

31:58.618 --> 32:01.021
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

32:01.054 --> 32:03.189
...JOE WENT BONKERS
IN THE DORM.

32:03.223 --> 32:08.595
ONE SECOND HE WAS JOKING,
AND THE NEXT HE'S CRYING,

32:08.628 --> 32:11.664
RUNNING THROUGH THE HALLWAYS
RIPPING OFF ALL HIS CLOTHES,

32:11.698 --> 32:12.899
RANTING AND RAVING.

32:12.932 --> 32:15.068
YOU KNOW, THE COACHES -- THEY
TRIED TO GET HIM UNDER CONTROL.

32:15.101 --> 32:16.336
THEY LITERALLY
TRIED TO SIT ON HIM,

32:16.369 --> 32:18.738
BUT, I MEAN, HE'S SCRATCHING,
CLAWING AT HIS ARMS.

32:18.772 --> 32:22.208
THE NEXT THING, HE'S -- HE'S
SMASHING WINDOWS WITH HIS FISTS.

32:22.242 --> 32:25.211
THERE WAS...

32:26.680 --> 32:29.015
THERE WAS GLASS
A-AND BLOOD EVERYWHERE.

32:29.049 --> 32:32.519
HOW DO YOU KNOW ALL OF THIS
IN SUCH GREAT DETAIL?

32:35.555 --> 32:37.590
BECAUSE I WAS THERE.

32:41.561 --> 32:46.032
THE POLICE CAME...

32:46.066 --> 32:48.635
TOOK HIM AWAY
IN HANDCUFFS.

32:48.668 --> 32:51.037
AND THEN?

32:51.071 --> 32:53.640
AND THEN JOE DROPPED OUT
OF THE ACADEMY.

32:53.673 --> 32:57.043
HE WASN'T DRAFTED, AND...

32:57.077 --> 33:00.113
AND I NEVER SAW HIM
AGAIN.

33:00.146 --> 33:03.750
AND THEN YOU MISSED
TWO WEEKS OF SCHOOL.

33:03.783 --> 33:07.387
I WAS SICK.

33:07.420 --> 33:09.756
YOU WERE TRAUMATIZED.

33:09.789 --> 33:13.226
AND I THINK THAT
YOU STILL ARE, HUTCH.

33:13.259 --> 33:15.161
I BELIEVE
THAT YOU ARE SUFFERING

33:15.195 --> 33:20.166
FROM AN UNDIAGNOSED FORM OF
POST-TRAUMATIC STRESS DISORDER.

33:20.200 --> 33:23.536
AND YOUR FEAR
OF ENDING UP LIKE CRABCHEK --

33:23.570 --> 33:23.636
IT'S LEADING TO
A SELF-FULFILLING PROPHECY.

33:28.241 --> 33:30.310
OKAY, BUT IF
THE GREAT JOE CRABCHEK

33:30.343 --> 33:33.580
CAN'T HANDLE
THE PRESSURE THEN...

33:33.613 --> 33:35.582
HOW THE HELL CAN I?

33:35.615 --> 33:39.686
YOUR DESTINY
IS YOUR OWN.

33:39.719 --> 33:44.124
YOU'RE DARRYL HUTCHINSON,
NOT JOE CRABCHEK.

33:44.157 --> 33:46.793
AND YOU'VE ALREADY TAKEN
A CRUCIAL STEP

33:46.826 --> 33:49.229
THAT CRABCHEK
NEVER DID.

33:49.262 --> 33:51.164
WHAT'S THAT?

33:51.197 --> 33:53.066
YOU'RE GETTING HELP.

33:56.603 --> 33:58.705
I WISH THAT YOU COULD STAY
AND COOK FOR ME FOREVER.

33:58.738 --> 34:00.240
LOOK AT US.

34:00.273 --> 34:02.609
I'M THE STAY-AT-HOME
COOKING MOM NOW.

34:02.642 --> 34:04.778
YOU'RE THE HOT WORKING WOMAN,
MEN AT EVERY PORT.

34:04.811 --> 34:05.078
GOD,
I MISS BEING A SAILOR.

34:07.447 --> 34:10.183
OH, GOD.
I MISS BEING A MOM.

34:10.216 --> 34:11.885
I MEAN,
MY DAUGHTER'S NEVER HOME,

34:11.918 --> 34:14.187
MY SON'S NEVER COMING HOME,
FAR AS I CAN TELL,

34:14.220 --> 34:17.390
AND I AM BACK TO POUNDING
THE PAVEMENT FOR WORK.

34:18.892 --> 34:22.796
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE WAY THINGS
TURNED OUT WITH THE HAWKS, DAN,

34:22.829 --> 34:24.330
BUT SILVER LINING --

34:24.364 --> 34:26.132
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
SEE MATT EVERY DAY

34:26.166 --> 34:27.634
AND PRETEND
YOU DON'T HATE HIM.

34:27.667 --> 34:29.402
I DON'T HATE HIM.

34:29.436 --> 34:32.739
I DON'T.
IT WAS TOTALLY AMICABLE.

34:32.772 --> 34:33.873
YOU KNOW, HE FELT LIKE

34:33.907 --> 34:35.375
HE OWED IT
TO NOELLE AND THE BABY

34:35.408 --> 34:38.378
TO SEE IF THEY COULD
MAKE THAT FAMILY WORK,

34:38.411 --> 34:40.180
AND, YOU KNOW,
SO DID I.

34:40.213 --> 34:43.249
BUT IT STILL SUCKS,
SO LET'S NOT PRETEND.

34:43.283 --> 34:45.251
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

34:45.285 --> 34:47.354
GUSTO? HI, BABY!

34:47.387 --> 34:49.923
NO, NO, I PUT THE EXTRA DIAPERS
IN THE GREY SUITCASE.

34:49.956 --> 34:51.257
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

34:56.830 --> 35:01.201
HELP ME, "OBI-WAN K'DANI."
YOU ARE MY ONLY HOPE.

35:01.234 --> 35:04.270
I'D BE HAPPY TO SCHEDULE YOU
AN APPOINTMENT AT A NORMAL HOUR,

35:04.304 --> 35:06.373
LIKE, SAY,
WHEN THE SUN IS UP.

35:06.406 --> 35:08.208
WHEN HAVE YOU EVER KNOWN ME
TO BE NORMAL?

35:08.241 --> 35:11.411
MM.
SPEAKING OF WHICH,
I QUIT.

35:12.812 --> 35:15.448
THE HAWKS.

35:15.482 --> 35:17.884
THAT MEANS I'M A FREE MAN --
A.K.A. UNEMPLOYED.

35:17.917 --> 35:20.520
[ SIGHS ]

35:20.553 --> 35:22.188
WHAT HAPPENED?

35:22.222 --> 35:23.923
COACH IS A DOUCHE.

35:23.957 --> 35:26.393
MATTY "D" IS A DOUCHE-B,
AND I GAVE MYSELF THE BAG.

35:26.426 --> 35:29.362
UPSIDE IS I CAN STILL
BE YOUR CLIENT.

35:29.396 --> 35:30.797
TERRENCE.

35:30.830 --> 35:32.766
ARE YOU SURE
THAT YOU'RE READY

35:32.799 --> 35:35.168
TO GIVE UP YOUR CAREER
WITH THE HAWKS?

35:36.503 --> 35:39.806
THERE WOULD PROBABLY BE
NO CAREER OR T.K. WITHOUT YOU.

35:39.839 --> 35:41.808
HE CAN'T JUST
TAKE YOU AWAY FROM ME.

35:41.841 --> 35:43.910
HE DOESN'T OWN ME.
IT'S NOT "DJANGO."

35:43.943 --> 35:46.212
OKAY, THAT'S WHAT
THIS IS ABOUT --

35:46.246 --> 35:47.547
YOU AND ME.

35:47.580 --> 35:49.416
MATTY D
DIDN'T FIGHT FOR YOU.

35:49.449 --> 35:52.552
HE LET COACH
BREAK UP THE BAND.

35:52.585 --> 35:55.221
YOU MAY NOT AGREE
WITH YOUR COACH OR HIS TACTICS,

35:55.255 --> 35:58.224
BUT HIS TRACK RECORD
IS PRETTY HARD TO ARGUE WITH.

35:58.258 --> 36:03.296
SO, IF YOU WANT THE RING,
THEN THIS MAY BE YOUR BEST SHOT.

36:03.329 --> 36:06.433
I KNOW
THIS IS DIFFICULT,

36:06.466 --> 36:11.338
BUT THERAPY ISN'T SUPPOSED
TO BE A FOREVER THING.

36:11.371 --> 36:11.438
OH, SO, NOW YOU'RE
BREAKING UP WITH ME, TOO?

36:14.974 --> 36:19.346
NO.
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

36:19.379 --> 36:24.317
BUT, TERRENCE, YOU HAVE COME
SO FAR IN THESE LAST TWO YEARS

36:24.351 --> 36:29.356
THAT MAYBE YOU ARE READY
TO FLY SOLO.

36:29.389 --> 36:32.459
* I KNOW IT'S A STRUGGLE

36:32.492 --> 36:34.961
* I KNOW THAT YOU'RE BLUE

36:34.994 --> 36:39.265
* YOU SHOULD KNOW
I'M HERE FOR YOU *

36:39.299 --> 36:42.268
SO, HOW WAS THE TRIP
TO K.C.?

36:42.302 --> 36:45.271
GOT ON AND OFF THE PLANE
WITH NO HICCUPS THANKS TO YOU.

36:45.305 --> 36:46.873
GOOD. HE SHOULD CONTINUE
TO IMPROVE.

36:46.906 --> 36:48.975
BUT HE NEEDS TO FIND
A GOOD THERAPIST IN KANSAS CITY.

36:49.009 --> 36:51.878
GREAT. ANYTHING ELSE?

36:51.911 --> 36:53.513
WELL, I WAS WONDERING

36:53.546 --> 36:56.282
WHY YOU NEVER MENTIONED
CRABCHEK'S MELTDOWN.

36:56.316 --> 36:58.985
DANI, WE LOST A KID --

36:59.019 --> 37:00.854
NOT SOMETHING
YOU LIKE TO DWELL ON.

37:00.887 --> 37:02.489
OKAY.

37:02.522 --> 37:03.957
Troy: CONNOR.
SIR.

37:03.990 --> 37:06.826
I JUST GOT WORD FROM K.C.
THEY'RE OUT.

37:06.860 --> 37:08.028
THEY HEARD ABOUT
HUTCH'S FLYING ISSUES,

37:08.061 --> 37:09.362
AND THEY GOT
COLD FEET.

37:09.396 --> 37:10.630
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN
FOR HUTCH?

37:10.663 --> 37:11.965
WELL, IT WOULD BE A DISASTER
IF I DIDN'T

37:13.633 --> 37:15.602
JUST GET OFF THE PHONE WITH
THE YANKEES FIVE MINUTES AGO.
AND?

37:15.635 --> 37:18.505
AND I CONVINCED THEM THAT HUTCH
WAS OF SOUND MIND AND BODY,

37:18.538 --> 37:19.906
AND THEY'RE GONNA
TAKE A FLIER ON HIM

37:19.939 --> 37:21.474
AT THE END
OF THE FIRST ROUND.

37:21.508 --> 37:24.477
YOU SON OF A BITCH.
YOU PULLED IT OFF.

37:24.511 --> 37:26.046
JUST DOING MY THING.

37:26.079 --> 37:28.381
OKAY, WAIT.
WHAT JUST HAPPENED?

37:31.551 --> 37:33.053
I'VE NEVER WON A RING --

37:33.086 --> 37:35.055
NOT IN HIGH SCHOOL,
NOT IN COLLEGE,

37:35.088 --> 37:36.823
AND DAMN SURE
NOT HERE IN THE PROS.

37:36.856 --> 37:39.826
JUST SO I'M CLEAR...

37:39.859 --> 37:41.528
THIS IS AN APOLOGY?

37:41.561 --> 37:44.431
I WILL DO WHATEVER IT TAKES
TO GET ONE.

37:44.464 --> 37:47.534
YOU SEE THOSE?

37:47.567 --> 37:49.636
THERE IS A METHOD

37:49.669 --> 37:52.472
TO WHAT APPEARS TO BE
MY MADNESS, MR. KING.

37:52.505 --> 37:55.542
THINK OF THIS SEASON
AS A TRUST EXERCISE.

37:55.575 --> 37:59.045
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS FALL BACK.

37:59.079 --> 38:01.081
I'LL HANDLE THE REST.

38:04.417 --> 38:06.419
JUST SO YOU KNOW --

38:06.453 --> 38:10.590
THERE WON'T BE
ANY MORE SECOND CHANCES.

38:12.125 --> 38:14.461
Connor: WE WERE NEVER THRILLED
ABOUT THE KID GOING TO K.C. --

38:14.494 --> 38:16.563
SMALL MARKET,
UNLIKELY TO COMPETE.

38:16.596 --> 38:18.665
LOWER DRAFT SLOT
MEANS LESS MONEY UP FRONT,

38:18.698 --> 38:21.067
BUT HE'LL PULL DOWN A HUNDRED
TIMES MORE IN ENDORSEMENTS

38:21.101 --> 38:22.702
IF HE WORKS OUT
HERE IN NEW YORK.

38:22.736 --> 38:26.072
SO YOU LEAKED THE FEAR OF FLYING
TO K.C. TO SCARE THEM OFF,

38:26.106 --> 38:28.441
AND THEN HOPED
THAT I WOULD FIX HUTCH

38:28.475 --> 38:30.543
IN TIME FOR THE DRAFT
AND FOR THE YANKEES.

38:30.577 --> 38:32.112
NICO SAID YOU WERE THE BEST.
HE DIDN'T LIE.

38:32.145 --> 38:33.446
HEY,
SINCE HUTCH IS STAYING HERE,

38:33.480 --> 38:35.615
CAN HE CONTINUE
TO SEE YOU?
YES.

38:35.648 --> 38:37.617
HERE IS MY CARD.

38:37.650 --> 38:39.986
DON'T NEED TO SEND A LIMO.
JUST HAVE HUTCH CALL ME.

38:40.020 --> 38:41.955
DULY NOTED.

38:43.923 --> 38:46.726
SANTINO.
PROPOSITION FOR YOU.

38:46.760 --> 38:48.094
WHAT?

38:48.128 --> 38:50.730
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE?

38:50.764 --> 38:52.399
[ LAUGHS ]

38:52.432 --> 38:54.034
WHAT KIND OF PROPOSITION
IS THAT?

38:54.067 --> 38:57.470
I'M OFFERING YOU A JOB --
HERE AT V3.

38:57.504 --> 38:59.606
YOU'LL HAVE YOUR OWN OFFICE,
ASSISTANT,

38:59.639 --> 39:01.975
EXPENSE ACCOUNT,
UNLIMITED RESOURCES.

39:02.008 --> 39:04.411
I'M FLATTERED,
BUT I JUST GOT OUT OF A WHOLE --

39:04.444 --> 39:05.912
YOU'LL DO THE MOST INTERESTING
WORK OF YOUR CAREER

39:05.945 --> 39:07.414
WITH THE MOST INTERESTING
PEOPLE ON THE PLANET.

39:07.447 --> 39:09.649
YOU'LL BE WELL COMPENSATED,
WELL TAKEN CARE OF,

39:09.683 --> 39:11.651
AND EXTREMELY APPRECIATED.
YES OR YES?

39:11.685 --> 39:14.154
[ LAUGHS ] OH, BOY.
YOU REALLY ARE GOOD.

39:14.187 --> 39:15.755
WHAT'S THE CATCH?

39:15.789 --> 39:18.491
CLOSE YOUR PRIVATE PRACTICE
AND BE EXCLUSIVE TO V3.

39:18.525 --> 39:20.727
OH.

39:20.760 --> 39:24.097
SANTINO, I SPOT GREATNESS
FOR A LIVING.

39:24.130 --> 39:25.932
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
YOU'RE AN ALL-STAR.

39:25.965 --> 39:27.667
TIME FOR YOU TO PLAY
ON AN ALL-STAR TEAM.

39:27.701 --> 39:30.470
WE COULD DO GREAT THINGS
TOGETHER.

39:30.503 --> 39:32.072
WHAT ARE YOU AFRAID OF,
SANTINO?

39:33.139 --> 39:35.075
FLYING?

39:41.648 --> 39:42.982
HEY.

39:43.583 --> 39:44.784
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

39:44.818 --> 39:46.619
YOU HAVE A MINUTE?

39:46.653 --> 39:47.954
YEAH.

39:49.823 --> 39:51.758
I JUST WANTED YOU
TO KNOW THAT, UM,

39:51.791 --> 39:54.594
I WENT TO BAT FOR YOU
WITH WIZINSKI,

39:54.627 --> 39:56.529
AND NO DEAL
TO BE HAD THERE.

39:56.563 --> 39:57.664
OH. [ LAUGHS ]

39:58.798 --> 40:00.967
WELL, I APPRECIATE THAT,
BUT IT WAS TOTALLY UNNECESSARY.

40:01.001 --> 40:05.638
NO. NO, IT WAS NECESSARY.
T.K. WAS RIGHT.

40:05.672 --> 40:08.975
YOU HAVE BEEN
AS VALUABLE TO THAT TEAM

40:09.009 --> 40:10.910
AS ANYONE
WHO'S COME THROUGH.

40:10.944 --> 40:14.681
CHANGE IS THE ONLY
CONSTANT, RIGHT?

40:15.915 --> 40:19.152
BUT...YOU DIDN'T COME OVER HERE
TO TELL ME SOMETHING

40:19.185 --> 40:21.688
I ALREADY KNEW,
DID YOU?

40:22.956 --> 40:24.691
I'M LEAVING THE HAWKS.

40:24.724 --> 40:27.093
WHAT?

40:28.828 --> 40:30.063
WHEN?

40:30.096 --> 40:32.065
RIGHT AWAY. TOMORROW.

40:32.098 --> 40:34.801
GOING TO BE THE G.M.
FOR BOSTON.

40:34.834 --> 40:37.804
BEEN COURTING ME
FOR A WHILE.

40:37.837 --> 40:39.139
BOSTON'S NOELLE'S HOMETOWN,

40:39.172 --> 40:41.841
SO IT ALL SEEMED
TO MAKE SENSE, YOU KNOW?

40:41.875 --> 40:44.944
CONGRATULATIONS.
THAT'S -- WOW.

40:44.978 --> 40:48.081
THAT IS A --
THAT'S A BIG CHANGE.

40:48.114 --> 40:50.650
GUESS WE'RE BOTH
MOVING ON.

40:53.620 --> 40:57.657
SORRY, DANI...

40:57.691 --> 40:58.958
FOR EVERYTHING.

40:58.992 --> 41:03.163
[ Voice breaking ]
THERE'S NO APOLOGIES REQUIRED.

41:06.132 --> 41:08.702
I WISH YOU SO MUCH LUCK.

41:08.735 --> 41:10.704
YOU TOO.

41:18.211 --> 41:20.847
OH, YEAH.

41:20.880 --> 41:23.049
* LOVING YOU

41:23.083 --> 41:27.754
* ISN'T THE RIGHT THING TO DO

41:29.789 --> 41:36.029
* HOW CAN I EVER CHANGE
THINGS THAT I FEEL *

41:37.897 --> 41:46.039
* IF I COULD,
MAYBE I'D GIVE YOU MY WORLD *

41:46.072 --> 41:53.046
* HOW CAN I WHEN YOU WON'T
TAKE IT FROM ME? *

41:55.015 --> 41:59.853
* YOU CAN GO YOUR OWN WAY

41:59.886 --> 42:03.757
* DON'T GO AWAY

42:03.790 --> 42:09.863
* YOU CAN CALL IT
ANOTHER LONELY DAY *

42:09.896 --> 42:11.865
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

42:11.898 --> 42:20.240
* YOU CAN CALL IT
ANOTHER LONELY DAY *

42:20.273 --> 42:24.210
* YOU CAN GO YOUR OWN WAY
WELCOME TO THE FAMILY,
DR. SANTINO.

42:24.244 --> 42:25.679
[ LAUGHS ] COME SAY HI.

42:25.712 --> 42:29.015
* GO YOUR OWN WAY

42:29.049 --> 42:30.216
* YOU CAN CALL IT
ANOTHER LONELY DAY *

42:30.250 --> 42:32.185
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
THIS WAS A ONE-TIME DEAL.

42:32.218 --> 42:35.989
YEAH, WE HAD
A CHANGE OF PLANS.

42:36.022 --> 42:37.190
* HEY, HEY, HEY
WE NEED SOMEONE
LIKE HER.

42:37.223 --> 42:38.892
* HEY, HEY, HEY
SHE'S NOSY.

42:38.925 --> 42:41.094
* HEY, HEY, HEY
SHE'S EFFECTIVE.

42:41.127 --> 42:42.996
* HEY, HEY, HEY

42:43.029 --> 42:44.998
* HEY, HEY, HEY

42:45.031 --> 42:47.100
* HEY, HEY, HEY
YEAH, IT'S ME.

42:47.133 --> 42:49.336
* HEY, HEY, HEY
WE HAVE A PROBLEM.

42:49.369 --> 42:59.746
* HEY, HEY, HEY

42:59.779 --> 43:09.823
* HEY, HEY, HEY

43:09.823 --> 43:22.202
* HEY, HEY, HEY
